Racing Teams Consider Taking Stake in Formula One Series, Independent Says

-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 
2011-09-15T01:59:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/racing-teams-consider-taking-stake-in-formula-one-series-independent-says.html
Grand prix racing teams have hired
DC Advisory Partners Ltd. to evaluate the possibility of their
acquiring a stake in Formula One, owned by CVC Partners Ltd.,
the Independent reported, citing Martin Whitmarsh, chairman of
the Formula One Teams Association and principal in McLaren
Automotive Ltd.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Simpson at 
 jsimpson12@bloomberg.net  